						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone near the temple of Basavaṇṇa.</hi></p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra—A.D. 1297.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">29th year</hi> of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Rāmachandrarāya, Hēmaḷambi, Mārgaśira ba. Pūrṇimā</hi> (mistake for <hi rend="italic">amāvāsyā</hi>) <hi rend="bold">Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1297, December 15, Sunday.</hi> It states that the hero-stone was erected in memory of <hi rend="bold">Maidhaya,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Kurubara Basava-gauṇḍa</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Iṭṭage.</hi></p>						

